Evaluate Google DeepMind EmbeddingGemma-300M, the SOTA sub-500M parameter embedding model.

## Model Details
- Source: Google DeepMind (released October 2025)
- Parameters: 308M
- Architecture: Modified Gemma with embedding-optimized training
- Dimensions: 768 (supports MRL truncation to 256/384/512)
- Context: 2048 tokens
- MTEB: Reported 55+ on retrieval (state-of-the-art for size class)
- Speed: Sub-15ms on EdgeTPU; estimated 30-80ms on modern CPU

## Why This Model Is Critical
EmbeddingGemma represents Google best effort at a tiny-but-powerful embedding model:
1. MRL support: Truncate to 256 dims with minimal quality loss
2. Instruction-tuned: Different prefixes for queries vs documents
3. Strong on short text: Optimized for mobile/edge = good for tweets
4. ONNX exportable: Should work with ort crate

## Architecture
```rust
pub struct EmbeddingGemmaEmbedder {
    session: ort::Session,
    tokenizer: tokenizers::Tokenizer,
    native_dims: usize,          // 768
    target_dims: Option<usize>,  // MRL truncation target
    max_length: usize,           // 2048 tokens
    mode: GemmaMode,             // Query vs Document
    name: String,
}

enum GemmaMode {
    Query,     // Prefixes with "Represent this query for retrieval: "
    Document,  // Prefixes with "Represent this document for retrieval: "
}

impl Embedder for EmbeddingGemmaEmbedder {
    fn embed_batch(&self, texts: &[&str]) -> Result<Vec<Vec<f32>>> {
        // 1. Apply instruction prefix based on mode
        let prefixed: Vec<String> = texts.iter().map(|t| {
            match self.mode {
                GemmaMode::Query => format!("Represent this query for retrieval: {}", t),
                GemmaMode::Document => format!("Represent this document for retrieval: {}", t),
            }
        }).collect();

        // 2. Tokenize with padding
        let encodings = self.tokenizer.encode_batch(
            prefixed.iter().map(|s| s.as_str()).collect::<Vec<_>>(),
            true
        )?;

        // 3. Run ONNX inference (transformer forward pass)
        let max_len = encodings.iter().map(|e| e.len()).max().unwrap_or(0)
            .min(self.max_length);
        let input_ids = build_padded_tensor(&encodings, max_len, 0);
        let attention_mask = build_attention_mask(&encodings, max_len);

        let outputs = self.session.run(ort::inputs![
            "input_ids" => input_ids,
            "attention_mask" => attention_mask,
        ]?)?;

        // 4. Pool: mean of last hidden state (respecting attention mask)
        let hidden = outputs[0].extract_tensor::<f32>()?;
        let mut results = Vec::with_capacity(texts.len());
        for i in 0..texts.len() {
            let mut pooled = mean_pool_with_mask(&hidden, i, max_len, self.native_dims, &attention_mask);

            // 5. MRL truncation if specified
            if let Some(target) = self.target_dims {
                pooled.truncate(target);
            }
            l2_normalize(&mut pooled);
            results.push(pooled);
        }
        Ok(results)
    }

    fn dimensions(&self) -> usize { self.target_dims.unwrap_or(self.native_dims) }
    fn model_name(&self) -> &str { &self.name }
    fn supports_mrl(&self) -> bool { true }
}
